    // Function implementation...
}
```

You can make it accessible from the `ui` package by defining an alias in `ui/ui.go`:

```go
package ui

import "github.com/knackwurstking/ui/components"

// Forward the AssetURL function to the public UI package API
var (
    AssetURL = components.AssetURL
)
```

This way, any code that imports the `ui` package can use `ui.AssetURL` directly without needing to go through the `components` package explicitly.

However, it seems you've already done this with your existing `AssetURL` variable in the `ui` package:

```go
