```

If `AssetURL` is already a public function or method in the `components` package, and you want to use it directly from your `ui` package without going through the `components` namespace, you can simply define an alias as shown above. If `AssetURL` is not public in the `components` package, you'll need to modify the visibility of that function to make it accessible from outside the `components` package.

Keep in mind, this kind of forwarding or aliasing is a common practice when designing Go packages to provide a clean and intuitive public API while reusing internal or lower-level functions.
